article.headline: Portland State 88, Montana State 82 (OT)
article.story: BOZEMAN, Mont. (AP) -- Jake Schroeder scored eight points in overtime to lead Portland State to the Big Sky Conference regular-season title Thursday night with an 88-82 victory over Montana State. Schroeder hit two consecutive three-point shots to open the overtime period and give the Vikings (19-7, 11-2 Big Sky) an 81-75 lead with 3:39 left. Montana State(13-13, 8-5) pulled to 85-81 on Branden Miller's layup with 1:02 remaining, but a free throw by Will Funn with 58 seconds left gave Portland State an 86-81 lead. Miller hit one of two free throws to pull the Bobcats to 86-82 with 41.2 seconds left, but Schroeder ensured the victory with a pair of free throws with 26.6 seconds left. Portland State hit only 4-of-14 free throws in overtime. Trailing 75-69 following Funn's free throw with 2:45 left in regulation, the Bobcats scored six straight points to send the game into the extra period. Marvin Moss hit his first field goal of the night with 2:25 left to cut the lead to 75-71. Two free throws by Nick Dissly pulled MSU to 75-73 with two minutes remaining. Miller got loose for a layup down the lane to tie the game with just over 22 seconds to go. PSU's Seamus Boxley, who scored 16 of his 20 points in the second half, missed a 3-pointer with two seconds left. Al Beye was 8-of-8 from the field for Montana State and led all scorers with 24 points. Ja'Ron Jefferson scored 17, Dissly had 15 and Miller finished with 11. Blake Walker led the Vikings with 21 points. Schroeder had 17 and Funn scored 11.
